Package: local-lucy
Version: @VERSION@
Section: misc
Priority: optional
Architecture: amd64
Depends: bash, python3, python3-venv, python3-pip, curl
Recommends: ffmpeg
Suggests: ollama
Installed-Size: @INSTALLED_SIZE@
Maintainer: Mike Perry <mike@michaelperry.cloud>
Homepage: https://github.com/mikemichaelperry-cloud/Local-Lucy
Description: Local Lucy v10 — self-learning, privacy-first desktop AI assistant
 Local Lucy is a privacy-first, locally-run AI assistant for Linux desktops.
 It combines a PySide6 HMI, Python intent router, local LLM integration via
 Ollama, and optional local voice/TTS.  This package installs the application
 to /opt/local-lucy and provides local-lucy / local-lucy-chat launchers.
